Genre DEMO:SVM Radial OneVsOne

This is the demo for solve Genre problematic. In order to well understand it, this file was resumed to only show up the data partition and model test.

About this set: - Two class, Others and Rock; - Others contains among genres known, anothers genres that were not categorized. - Rock are songs that contains the aggretion of subgenre of Rock; - The data has not discretes values; - tempo, energy, danceability, etc are song features; - Duration is not take in consideration on thoses models; - We use 2% of Others, because it has 40k of songs. Thus we choose reduce others class. - We are using for test and train datasets random proportional partitions;

Considerations: - test set has a size of 30%; - train set has a size of 70%;

Strategies: - One vs One; - Supervised Classification;

Models: - SVM Radial; - SVM Linear; - KNN; - Naive Bayne;

Main goal of the best model: - Classify/Predict new instances using these models; - Find the must importance features; - Find the best model possible;

Vocabulary:

discrete values : ( Binary values like 0/1, yes/no, true/false )

formula :

The variable on the left-hand side of a tilde (~) is called the dependent variable(response variable, outcome variable or label), while the variables on the right-hand side are called the independent variables (predictor (variable), controlled variable, feature) and are joined by plus signs +.

+ : for adding terms; - : for removing terms;

Music Map: https://musicmap.info/

# Run algorithms using 10-fold cross validation
control <- trainControl(method="cv", number=10)
metric <- "Accuracy"
#+tempo+energy+danceability+speechiness+accoustiness+loudness+duration+valence+instrumentalness
formula_SVM <- genretype~ .
#SVM Linear 
set.seed(89)
fit.svmLinear_train <- train(formula_SVM,
                             data = train_Rock,
                             method = "svmLinear",
                             trControl=control,
                             preProcess = c("center", "scale"),
                             tuneLength = 10)
